## 🧠 CORE GAMEPLAY SPECIFICATION (DO NOT ALTER)

### 1. PLAYER & CONTROLS  
- **Movement:** W/S forward/backward; A/D strafe left/right  
- **Turning:** Mouse movement (pointer lock) for smooth 360° rotation  
- **Virus Capture:** Press `C` when near a virus (within ~2 tiles)  
- **Quarantine Sequence:** Press `V` while stationary  
- **Node Cleaning:** Stand on infected node for ~8s to purge infection; movement breaks it  

### 2. RULES SYSTEM  
| ID | Name              | Type      | Duration / Cooldown       | Effect                                                                 |
|----|-------------------|-----------|---------------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| [1]| FIREWALL IS WALL  | Toggle    | Persistent / 10s CD       | Rule ON by default; Firewalls (tile 2) become solid *only* when ON   |
| [2]| NODES ARE LOCKED  | Duration  | 5s active / 60s CD        | Nodes cannot be infected, cleaned, or interacted with                 |
| [3]| VIRUS IS STOP     | Duration  | 3.5s active / 60s CD      | All viruses freeze in place            |
| [4]| VIRUS IS SLOW     | Duration  | 8s active / 30s CD        | Viruses move at 60% speed                                              |

> ⚠️ **Important:** Rule toggles and durations must be handled by a centralized `rulesManager` class.

### 3. OBJECTIVES & WIN/LOSS  
- Start with: 5 nodes (1 secure), 3 active viruses, health = 100%  
- **Win condition:** Quarantine all 3 viruses AND ≥4 nodes remain uninfected  
- **Lose conditions:** All nodes infected OR player HP ≤ 0  

### 4. INFECTION EFFECTS (STACKING)  
Each infected node imposes a unique penalty—effects *stack* with multiple infections:

| Node ID | Name              | Effect                                                                 |
|---------|-------------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| 0       | Motor Control     | Movement speed reduced by 50%                                          |
| 1       | Visual Processor  | Screen shake + subtle visual distortion (e.g., chromatic aberration)  |
| 2       | Auditory Processing | RGB static overlay on HUD; mini-map corrupted or hidden             |
| 3       | Neural Link       | Rule toggle activation delayed by ~1500ms                               |
| 4       | Life Support      | -0.5 HP/sec drain AND healing blocked (coolant, nodes, etc.)          |

> ✅ Healing only works on secure Life Support node (+2 HP/s).

### 5. TILE & ENTITY TYPES  
Use the following tile IDs in your map data (`0` = empty, `1` = wall, etc.):

| ID | Type         | Behavior                                                                 |
|----|--------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| 0  | EMPTY        | Walkable                                                                 |
| 1  | WALL         | Always solid                                                             |
| 2  | FIREWALL     | Solid *only* when Rule [1] is ON                                         |
| 3  | COOLANT      | Continuously heals player                                                |
| 4  | RULE_BLOCK   | Virus interaction point; can toggle Rule [1] OFF                         |
| 5  | SYSTEM_NODE  | Objective node. Can be infected, cleaned, or secured                     |
| 6–8| WALL_VARIANTS| Visual only (same collision as `WALL`)                                   |

> 🗺️ **Map Size:** Exactly 64×64 tiles. Each tile = 64px → canvas internal resolution = 4096×4096 (scaled via CSS).

